\f0\b \cf0 Create Until "Recent" Cache Full:
\f1\b0  Located under the "Pattern" menu (and in the Dock menu for StarfishX), selecting this option will cause StarfishX to generate new patterns continuously until StarfishX has created enough patterns to fill the "recent" cache (the number of patterns specified by the "Keep N most recent patterns" option). Note that patterns generated this way are not installed on the desktop by StarfishX. You may go back later and install any pattern(s) you like with the "Review recent patterns" controls. Note that once this command has completed, you will not be able to run it again until you delete some patterns or increase the number of recent patterns StarfishX tracks.\
\
Once you have the options set the way you like, press the "New Pattern" button to start StarfishX generating a new pattern for each monitor specified. If you have selected the "Quit when finished" option, Starfish will automatically terminate when it has generated the final pattern requested.\
\
All of the options you specify here will be saved when you quit StarfishX.\
\
