Editing Palettes
\f1\b0\fs24 \ulnone \
StarfishX starts off with a set of about a dozen default palettes. Using the "Edit..." option under the "Palette:" popup menu, you may edit or remove any of the default palettes, and add your own custom palettes for StarfishX to use. The interface is fairly straightforward. However, keep in mind the following notes about how StarfishX uses these palettes:\
\
1) A palette must contain at least two colors.\
2) Not all colors in a palette will be used by all patterns. The 
\f0\b number
\f1\b0  of colors (as well as 
\f0\b which
\f1\b0  colors) used is determined randomly for each pattern. Palettes with lots (more than about eight) will rarely use all the colors available for any given pattern.\

